  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">COVID19 relief to 4,000 migrant workers Bangalore</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The plight of India&apos;s migrant workers in the COVID 19 lockdown was highlighted on international news channels.  Overnight migrant workers found themselves unable to work and not able to return to their villages. They are effectively trapped in migrant worker camps with no money, food, work or real chances of social distancing.  To prevent hunger and destitution in Bangalore&apos;s migrant communities, Sampark plans to distribute essential food and provision to 12000 migrant workers and their families</narrative>
  </description>
